list.abstract: central（英、美[ˈsentrəl]），英语单词，作形容词用，意思为中心的；中央的；最重要的。短语搭配有central park（中央公园），例句为“He travelled to an orphanage in Guatemala in Central America.（他去了中美洲危地马拉的一家孤儿院。）” central形容词类近义词有nuclear、primary、major等，相关反义词有peripheral，名词形式为centre、centralist。

yingyinNormal.en: Central Park? Yeah. All of us. All day.
yingyinNormal.zh: 中央公园？对，大家一起，去个一整天。

yingyinNormal.en: Closer to earth is Grand Central Terminal.
yingyinNormal.zh: 靠近地面的是大中央车站。

yingyinNormal.en: The West End in central London is a story in itself.
yingyinNormal.zh: 而伦敦中部的西区则又拥有另一个故事。

yingyinNormal.en: Well, we thought we would all go to a picnic in Central Park.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我们可以一起去野餐，就去中央公园。

yingyinNormal.en: I'm going home to bask in the triumph of my Central Park idea.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我决定回家反省这个烂主意。

yingyinNormal.en: This is California's central valley,and my guide is farmer Ted Sheeley.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这里是加利福尼亚的中央山谷，我的向导是农场主泰德·舍利。

yingyinNormal.en: These are onion fields in Central California. Remember farmer Ted Sheeley?
yingyinNormal.zh: 这些是加州中部的洋葱田。还记得农场主泰德·舍利吗?

yingyinNormal.en: I'm gonna reverse what I said. Central Park dog rentals, million-dollar idea.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我要收回我说的话，中央公园租狗生意——能大赚特赚的点子。

yingyinNormal.en: They're like its central nervous system. But this is the brain. It controls them all.
yingyinNormal.zh: 就像中枢神经系统一样，而这个，就是大脑，它们的指挥部。

yingyinNormal.en: What'll we high-five about at the stupid Central Park? It's right by my house. All right.
yingyinNormal.zh: 大家去中央公园有什么好兴奋，“好耶，就在我家旁边”。

yingyinNormal.en: And what kind of a man shows up to a date in board shorts? It's Central America. It's hot.
yingyinNormal.zh: 另外，什么样的男人会穿着沙滩裤去约会？这是中美洲，热得很。

yingyinNormal.en: The assignment was to paint a photorealistic representation of the benches in Central Park.
yingyinNormal.zh: 作业是画一幅像相片一样逼真的中央公园的长椅。

yingyinNormal.en: Explore the malls and futuristic architecture of Hong Kong's main business district, Central.
yingyinNormal.zh: 在香港的主要商业区中环，您可以游走各大大小小的商场和富有未来感的建筑物。

yingyinNormal.en: And the only way to download the ledger is through the central computer terminal located there.
yingyinNormal.zh: 下载这个账册的唯一方法就是通过那地方的中央计算机终端。

yingyinNormal.en: And yet, here we have the Central Intelligence Agency indicating otherwise. I don't understand.
yingyinNormal.zh: 但是，中情局说明的情况好像并不是这样。我不太明白。

yingyinNormal.en: Because it's not all laughing, happy, candy in the sky, drinking coffee at Central Perk all the time.
yingyinNormal.zh: 因为婚姻不是只有欢乐，只有梦幻，只管上咖啡馆。

yingyinNormal.en: At the end of the day, let the outdoor escalators on Central carry you up to the midlevel neighborhoods.
yingyinNormal.zh: 日落时份，不妨乘搭中环的户外电梯走到中半山区。

yingyinNormal.en: Actually, he's buying a much bigger place. It's got a great view of Central Park. That's enough out of you.
yingyinNormal.zh: 他要买一间更大的公寓 景观很棒，可以看到中央公园。你说够了！

yingyinNormal.en: Westerly winds kick up condensation, forming cumulonimbus clouds which begin to revolve around a central axis.
yingyinNormal.zh: 西风激起冷凝作用，生成以中央轴心旋转的积雨云。

yingyinNormal.en: Well, relax. If it makes you feel any better, I've attended some of the fine medical schools in Central America.
yingyinNormal.zh: 放轻松，我在中美洲念过很好的医学院，这样你比较安心了吧。
